The Committee remains concerned with ICE’s financial manage-
ment practices, detailed in GAO–24–106550, ‘‘Additional Steps
Needed to Improve ICE’s Budget Projections and Execution,’’ which
have led to an inappropriate and disproportionate reliance on re-
programming and transfer authority to ensure solvency at the end
of any given fiscal year over the past decade. Actions already taken
in fiscal year 2025 are especially egregious—ICE began spending
more than its appropriated level shortly after the fiscal year com-
menced and operations now far exceed available resources. In order
to sustain this heightened operational tempo, ICE has and will
likely continue to use the bill’s transfer and reprogramming au-
thority to the maximum extent, once again taking from other com-
ponents’ operational priorities.
