Mission
The United States Secret Service (USSS or ‘‘the Secret Service’’)
protects and investigates threats against the President and Vice
President, their families, visiting heads of state, and other des-
ignated individuals; protects the White House, the Vice President’s
Residence, foreign missions, and certain other facilities within
Washington, D.C.; and coordinates the security at National Special
Security Events (NSSEs). The Secret Service also investigates vio-
lations of laws relating to counterfeiting of obligations and securi-
ties of the United States; financial crimes, including access device
fraud, financial institution fraud, identity theft, and computer
fraud; and computer-based attacks on financial, banking, and tele-
communications infrastructure. In addition, the agency provides
support for investigations related to missing and exploited children.
